Remarks. This species appears to be quite widespread. It has been found in several places in eastern Thailand to southern Laos (
Fig. 20
). The animals reveal the same morphological characters in all populations except the population from Ban Xanapho, Laos , in which the legs and antennae are carmine to light pink while their bodies larger (length 45.8–47.2 mm ). However, the width of midbody pro- and metazonae lies well within the species’ variation range ( 3.9 and 4.7 mm , 4.2 and 4.9 mm , respectively), so the Laotian population is attributed to this species.
